<TITLE> WB commits $1b to Dhaka by December </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com)  The World Bank has committed a $1 billion assistance package for Bangladesh by December this year. Finance and planning adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam, in Washington in connection with the annual World Bank-IMF meeting, on Saturday met with the Bangladesh country team led by the vice president South Asia region Isabel Guerrero, the finance ministry said. They reviewed the assistance package for Bangladesh for the current year and it was decided that four projects--Budgetary Support under the Global Food Crisis Response programme, Shiddhirganj Peaking Power Project, Dhaka Water Supply and Sanitation Project and Emergency 2007 Cyclone Recovery and Restoration--will be approved by the bank by the end of December. With these projects, World Bank's total commitment to Bangladesh by December 2008 will be nearly $1 billion, a record level of financial support for Bangladesh. The meeting also reviewed the likely projects to be taken up in the next year to utilise a World Bank aid envelope amounting to $1.3 billion in the next fiscal ye
